14:47.787 --> 14:50.423
What kind of food expert
DOESN'T want flavor?

14:50.490 --> 14:51.992
That's insane!

14:55.595 --> 14:57.197
I'm taking this out there.

14:57.264 --> 14:59.732
No! Zesty will hate it!

14:59.799 --> 15:02.035
You are going to
RUIN this for them!

15:02.102 --> 15:06.439
No! I'm trying to fix
it after YOU ruined it!

15:06.506 --> 15:09.376
Nooooooooooo!

15:09.442 --> 15:10.410
[splat]

15:13.546 --> 15:17.384
I think we are done here.

15:17.450 --> 15:20.988
Zesty! Please wait.
Allow me to explain.

15:21.054 --> 15:24.557
Rarity. When it comes to
fashion, you are adequate.

15:24.624 --> 15:27.127
But take some advice
from a friend.

15:27.194 --> 15:29.662
Keep your opinions
out of restaurants.

15:29.729 --> 15:33.766
Substandard food, laughable
service and I would think

15:33.833 --> 15:36.703
even YOU could recognize
that the decor here

15:36.769 --> 15:41.041
is trying desperately
while desperately failing.

15:41.108 --> 15:44.177
Recommending a disreputable
place such as this

15:44.244 --> 15:47.747
could do serious damage
to your social standing.

15:47.814 --> 15:49.149
Disreputable?

15:49.216 --> 15:52.419
You mean a place with food
that actually tastes good?

15:52.485 --> 15:55.755
Anypony can throw
ingredients together

15:55.822 --> 15:59.692
and create an obvious taste
that uncultured ponies

15:59.759 --> 16:02.062
like those two can register.

16:02.129 --> 16:03.530
Hey!

16:03.596 --> 16:06.366
But it takes a TRUE
culinary artist

16:06.433 --> 16:08.568
to create a subtle taste.

16:08.635 --> 16:11.671
The barest hint
of a sensation.

16:11.738 --> 16:15.575
That's what I bring to
Canterlot. That's art.

16:20.480 --> 16:23.216
I'm so embarrassed.

16:23.283 --> 16:25.485
I don't know that there are
words to adequately express

16:25.552 --> 16:28.088
how truly sorry we are.

16:28.155 --> 16:32.792
The worst has happened. No use
crying over spilled food now.

16:32.859 --> 16:36.396
Here, this always cheered
me up when I was younger.

16:36.463 --> 16:40.633
[gasp] My spicy flat
noodle soup! [slurps]

16:40.700 --> 16:46.339
Mmm! Oh my, this is
truly delightful.

16:46.406 --> 16:48.808
This is the best thing
you've made so far.

16:48.875 --> 16:51.478
And I thought the food
before was the best!

16:51.544 --> 16:54.314
That's all I've ever
wanted to do, Father.

16:54.381 --> 16:56.549
Make food for the
ponies of Canterlot

16:56.616 --> 17:00.187
like the food we made
together when I was younger.

17:00.253 --> 17:03.690
It has been so long since
we've cooked together. [laugh]

17:03.756 --> 17:05.758
Remember how you used
to hide the ingredients

17:05.825 --> 17:06.793
you did not like.

17:06.859 --> 17:09.662
[laugh]

17:09.729 --> 17:11.398
You know what?

17:11.464 --> 17:13.366
Who cares what
some stuffy unicorn

17:13.433 --> 17:16.236
thinks of the food
here. It's exquisite.

17:16.303 --> 17:18.171
That's true.

17:18.238 --> 17:20.240
And you don't need three
silly hooves in your window

17:20.307 --> 17:21.408
to prove it.

17:21.474 --> 17:23.310
That's double true!

17:23.376 --> 17:26.546
You just need ponies in
here to give it a chance.

17:26.613 --> 17:29.249
Ponies that will tell
everypony else in Canterlot

17:29.316 --> 17:31.718
that the Tasty Treat is
the best food in the city!

17:31.784 --> 17:34.354
THAT'S TRUE TIMES THREE!

17:34.421 --> 17:38.558
But without Zesty's approval,
nopony will even try our food.

17:38.625 --> 17:41.294
Oohoho, yes they will.

17:41.361 --> 17:44.164
Pinkie! We ARE the
perfect team for this;

17:44.231 --> 17:45.898
we were just doing
the wrong jobs.

17:45.965 --> 17:48.135
I will go out and
bring the crowd.

17:48.201 --> 17:51.271
You stay here and make sure
this place is every bit

17:51.338 --> 17:54.741
as unique and rustic as it
was the moment we walked in.

17:54.807 --> 17:56.643
And what about us?

17:56.709 --> 18:00.713
You two? You are going to
cook. Make whatever you want.

18:00.780 --> 18:03.750
And make a lot of it. I
intend to bring a crowd!

18:03.816 --> 18:06.453
* [upbeat Indian music] *

18:06.519 --> 18:10.157
Would the owner of one of the
premier boutiques in Canterlot

18:10.223 --> 18:11.924
put her stamp of
approval on something

18:11.991 --> 18:13.826
that wasn't fabulous?

18:13.893 --> 18:24.171
**

18:24.171 --> 18:32.645
**

18:35.848 --> 18:37.016
It's almost time.

18:37.083 --> 18:39.819
Is everypony ready for
the grand re-re-opening?

18:39.886 --> 18:43.890
Before we open, my father and
I just wanted to say thank you

18:43.956 --> 18:45.225
for all of your help.

18:45.292 --> 18:47.760
We've both been so stressed
about the restaurant

18:47.827 --> 18:50.630
succeeding that we forgot
what it was we loved about it

18:50.697 --> 18:52.031
in the first place.

18:52.098 --> 18:54.934
Cooking is something we
used to love to do together.

18:55.001 --> 18:56.736
No matter what happens next,

18:56.803 --> 18:59.439
thank you for
reminding us of that.

18:59.506 --> 19:02.642
Oh you guys! GROUP HUG!

19:02.709 --> 19:04.911
[grunt][laugh]

19:04.977 --> 19:08.315
Now come on! We've
got a party to throw!

19:10.683 --> 19:13.920
Oooh! Wow! It
smells really good!

19:13.986 --> 19:18.358
Welcome to the Tasty Treat!
Make yourselves comfortable!

19:24.731 --> 19:27.834
Please, feel free
to sample the food!

19:27.900 --> 19:29.736
Zesty: What's this?

19:29.802 --> 19:34.341
What is everypony doing here?
This place has no hooves.

19:34.407 --> 19:36.743
It is not in keeping
with the level of cuisine

19:36.809 --> 19:39.512
that I have set
for Canterlot.

19:39.579 --> 19:42.815
Nopony told you this
place was acceptable.

19:42.882 --> 19:46.719
Uh, Rarity and her friend said
it was good. They told us.

19:46.786 --> 19:51.491
They told you? And who are
they to tell you anything?

19:51.558 --> 19:55.027
Rarity can tell you what hats
to wear with which skirts.

19:55.094 --> 19:57.830
Her friend can tell you how
to maintain a tragic look

19:57.897 --> 19:59.666
for a frizzy mane.

19:59.732 --> 20:02.802
They can't tell you
what food you can eat.

20:02.869 --> 20:05.872
No, we can't. And
neither can you.

20:05.938 --> 20:08.675
Nopony has the right to tell
these ponies what to think.

20:08.741 --> 20:11.278
Zesty, you have very specific--

20:11.344 --> 20:12.479
And very strange!

20:12.545 --> 20:15.348
Yes and very strange
opinions about food.

20:15.415 --> 20:16.949
And that's your right.

20:17.016 --> 20:19.319
But just because you like
your food a certain way,

20:19.386 --> 20:20.920
there is no reason
to tell these ponies

20:20.987 --> 20:22.489
that they need to
do the same.

20:22.555 --> 20:24.023
Rarity is right!

20:24.090 --> 20:26.859
I for one think the
food here is delicious.

20:26.926 --> 20:29.796
I own the Smoked Oat
on Restaurant Row!

20:29.862 --> 20:32.031
I hate the food we make!

20:32.098 --> 20:36.769
From now on, it's all
smoked, basted and grilled!

20:36.836 --> 20:41.341
This food is an inspiration!
I own the Bake Shop!

20:41.408 --> 20:43.343
I'm going to bake my
mother's Bundt cake

20:43.410 --> 20:46.446
the way she made
it! Full of flavor!

20:46.513 --> 20:49.949
Yes! Yeah!

20:50.016 --> 20:52.852
Zesty, are you sure you
wouldn't like to try the food?

20:52.919 --> 20:55.455
Ignoring a unique and fresh
establishment such as this

20:55.522 --> 20:59.058
could do serious damage
to your social standing.

20:59.125 --> 21:00.727
[huffs]

21:02.729 --> 21:03.896
[slam]

21:04.931 --> 21:09.035
[cheers]

21:09.101 --> 21:10.903
Thank you so much!

21:10.970 --> 21:13.473
You are both truly amazing.

21:13.540 --> 21:18.578
**

21:18.645 --> 21:23.350
Nothing can stop the dynamic
duo of Pinkie and Rarity!

21:23.416 --> 21:27.987
[happy chattering]
